05282nam a22008655i 9783110759808DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831107598087 a10.1515/97831107598082doi  a(DE-B1597)589897  a(OCoLC)1342502405  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aBUS0300002bisacsh1 aGarti, Anat, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aWork–Family Triangle Synchronization :bEmployee, manager, and spouse /cAnat Garti, Shay Tzafrir. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (XIV, 128 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tAcknowledgments -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1 Work–Family Interface: An Overview -- tChapter 2 Work–Family Stakeholders -- tChapter 3 Work–Family Triangle’s Dyads -- tChapter 4 Triangling: The Triad Work–Family Relationship -- tChapter 5 Work–Family Triangle Synchronization (WFTS) -- tChapter 6 WFTS Psychological Contract -- tChapter 7 Building and Developing a Trust Triangle Relationship -- tSummary -- tList of Figures -- tList of Tables -- tAbout the Authors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  a"I need to check with my partner" is a common response of an employee to his manager, emphasizing the tug of war between the employee’s spouse and the workplace. The challenges in the fields of work and family have been the focus of researchers for decades. Frameworks for work–family conflict, work–family enrichment, and work–family balance have been put forth in light of the complexity of the interface. Yet the relationship between the three stakeholders managing the interface (manager, employee, and spouse), has not received the attention it deserves. Work–Family Triangle Synchronization takes a holistic look into the triangle of forces involved in the conflict: the manager, the employee, and the employee’s spouse at home. Using the therapeutic triangle relationship framework, it elaborates on the dynamic of work–family triangles and offers a structured process for designing a psychological contract among the three players. This process is termed work–family triangle synchronization (WFTS). Based on the authors’ 20 years of academic research and field experience in the organizational and family domains this book introduces a novel synchronization model, methodology, and compelling tools. Personal anecdotes and stories make the text accessible and understandable, accompanying the reader step by step in the task of developing a synchronized work–family triangle psychological contract, as both a diagnostic and a management tool.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aWork-Family-Konflikt. 4aWork-Life-Balance. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Human Resources & Personnel Management.2bisacsh  aPsychological Contract.  aTrust.  aWork–family Relationship.  aWork–life Balance.  aWork–life Conflict.1 aTzafrir, Shay, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 Englishz978311099282308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2022z9783110992922oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831107599830 cprintz978311075963140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075980840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110759808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110759808/original  a978-3-11-099282-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 En